2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of multiple access cognitive channels using ESPAR antennas, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system-level solution to improve the performance of multiple access cognitive channels, which is relevant to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of multiple access cognitive channels, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a computational technique to analyze the capacity of interference-limited multiple access channels, which is relevant to computational engineering, finance, and science.
